@page "/solutions/presales"
@layout MarketingLayout

<PageTitle>NavTour for Pre-sales Teams &mdash; NavTour</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="NavTour helps pre-sales engineers build, maintain, and personalize a scalable demo library so every AE can run a polished product proof without an SE in the room." />
</HeadContent>

<section class="nt-page-hero">
    <div class="nt-container">
        <span class="eyebrow">Solutions &middot; Pre-sales</span>
        <h1>A demo library your AEs can<br /><em>run without you in the room.</em></h1>
        <p class="lead">Pre-sales engineers build once. Sales teams personalize and deploy. Every buyer gets a polished, accurate demo — without bottlenecking the SE team.</p>
        <div class="nt-hero-actions">
            <a href="/register" class="btn btn-orange btn-lg">Start free &rarr;</a>
            <a href="/solutions" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">All use cases</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="nt-frames-section">
    <div class="nt-container">
        <article class="nt-frame-row">
            <div class="nt-frame-copy">
                <div class="num">01<span class="slash">/</span><span class="lbl">Demo library</span></div>
                <h3>One library, every persona,<br /><em>always current.</em></h3>
                <p>Pre-sales engineers capture the product once and publish demo variations for each persona — ops, finance, IT, executive. AEs pick the right version, personalize it, and send it without filing a ticket.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Demo Hub organized by persona, vertical, or use case</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Version control — update the master, all instances refresh</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Publish/unpublish controls for each variant</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-frame-visual">
                <span class="nt-frame-cap">Demo Hub &middot; SE-managed library</span>
                <div class="nt-frame-img">
                    <img src="/images/shots/hub.png" alt="Demo hub organized for presales" class="nt-lightbox" />
                </div>
                <div class="anno tl">
                    <div class="lbl">SE bottleneck eliminated</div>
                    <strong>AEs self-serve the right demo</strong>
                    <p>Filter by persona or vertical. Every demo is accurate and on-brand.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        <article class="nt-frame-row reverse">
            <div class="nt-frame-copy">
                <div class="num">02<span class="slash">/</span><span class="lbl">Personalization</span></div>
                <h3>Personalize at scale with<br /><em>tokens, not re-recordings.</em></h3>
                <p>Use <code style="font-family:var(--nt-mono);font-size:0.88em;background:rgba(251,173,72,0.18);padding:1px 5px;border-radius:4px">&#123;&#123;company&#125;&#125;</code> and <code style="font-family:var(--nt-mono);font-size:0.88em;background:rgba(251,173,72,0.18);padding:1px 5px;border-radius:4px">&#123;&#123;contact&#125;&#125;</code> tokens in every annotation. When the AE sends the link, they fill in the values and the demo renders personalized — no new recording needed.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Unlimited personalization variables per demo</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Pre-fill from CRM contact data via URL params</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Branching paths for different audience segments</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-frame-visual">
                <span class="nt-frame-cap">Editor &middot; personalization tokens</span>
                <div class="nt-frame-img">
                    <img src="/images/shots/player-step1.png" alt="Personalization tokens in a demo" class="nt-lightbox" />
                </div>
                <div class="anno br">
                    <div class="lbl">Scale without cloning</div>
                    <strong>One demo, 40 personalized sends</strong>
                    <p>Tokens render at view time. No duplicate demos cluttering the library.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        <article class="nt-frame-row">
            <div class="nt-frame-copy">
                <div class="num">03<span class="slash">/</span><span class="lbl">POC accelerator</span></div>
                <h3>Ship a proof-of-concept demo<br /><em>before the kickoff call.</em></h3>
                <p>Capture the prospect&rsquo;s use case in the product, annotate it with their workflow, and send it before the POC kickoff. They arrive with questions — not skepticism about whether NavTour can handle their scenario.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Custom showcase with prospect branding</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Track who from the buying committee viewed it</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Embed in the POC proposal doc</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-frame-visual">
                <span class="nt-frame-cap">Showcase &middot; POC kickoff</span>
                <div class="nt-frame-img">
                    <img src="/images/shots/showcases.png" alt="POC showcase for presales" class="nt-lightbox" />
                </div>
                <div class="anno tr">
                    <div class="lbl">Faster POC entry</div>
                    <strong>Prospects arrive with questions, not doubt</strong>
                    <p>Show the use case in advance. The kickoff becomes a configuration call.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

<NtCTABand Headline="Build the demo library your AEs have been asking for."
           SubText="Free to start. Your first demo library can be live before end of week."
           PrimaryLabel="Start free &rarr;"
           SecondaryLabel="See all solutions"
           SecondaryHref="/solutions" />
